This has been on my todo list for months. It allows you to do this:

```ts
import { createContext } from 'svelte';

interface Foo {
  // ...
}

export const [getFoo, setFoo] = createContext<Foo>();
```

```svelte
<script>
  import Child from './Child.svelte';
  import { setFoo } from '$lib/context';

  setFoo({...});
</script>

<Child />
```

```svelte
<!-- Child.svelte -->
<script>
  import { getFoo } from '$lib/context';

  const foo = getFoo();
</script>
```

This means you no longer need to worry about passing keys around, or typing the `getContext` return value.

