Alternative to #17374. I think this is a more correct fix — it makes the `$.hmr` block effect a no-op when it isn't running as a result of a `hot.accept` callback, rather than excluding _all_ block effects from re-running after the first `await` is encountered during traversal.

It also makes the HMR implementation simpler, both in terms of the generated code...

```js
if (import.meta.hot) {
	A = $.hmr(A, () => A[$.HMR].source);

	import.meta.hot.accept((module) => {
		module.default[$.HMR].source = A[$.HMR].source;
		$.set(A[$.HMR].source, module.default[$.HMR].original);
	});
}
```

```js
if (import.meta.hot) {
	A = $.hmr(A);

	import.meta.hot.accept((module) => {
		A[$.HMR](module.default);
	});
}
```

...and the dance that needs to happen inside `$.hmr`.

